  "name": "Recuperation [Mythic]",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/commodities/cloth/cloth-roll-gold-green.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The creature is restored to full hit points after 8 hours of rest so long as it isn&rsquo;t dead. In addition, by expending one use of <a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf-content.pf-universal-monster-rules\" data-id=\"emNdW1Y7gFdGwNpo\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">mythic power</span></a> and resting for 1 hour, it regains a number of hit points equal to half its full hit points (up to a maximum of its full hit points) and regain the use of any class features that are limited to a certain number of uses per day (such as barbarian rage, bardic performance, spells per day, and so on). This rest is treated as 8 hours of sleep for such abilities. This rest doesn&rsquo;t refresh uses of mythic power or any mythic abilities that are limited to a number of times per day.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Format</em>: recuperation</p>\n<p><em>Location</em>: SQ.</p>",
